{
  "stem": "14867.1",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Because my brother was studying in Warsaw.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And of course, he never wanted to admit it to us and-- but I learned later that mother knew, though she didn't didn't-- didn't tell us anything because she didn't want the children to worry about it.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But-- and of course, in Warsaw at that time, there were all kind of restrictions.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "First of all, it was unusual for a Jewish guy-- man-- to get into-- to law school, and it was very expensive.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And they could not sit on the same side with the students.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "The Jews had to sit separately, to the left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And very often there they encountered, already, antisemitism They couldn't live in the same dorm with Polish.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "They had their Jewish quarters.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And very often, some Jewish students were beat up without any reason.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So in the bigger cities, and especially among students, you already knew that there was antisemitism But personally, the family never cared.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "Never happened to us.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It is true that among peasants, especially Ukrainian peasants, there was a lot of antisemitism But the fear of a land loaner was so high that they wouldn't dare to show it-- show it off.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my father was the landlord.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But he was the so-called very good landlord, but still a landlord.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, when the war broke out and my father was afraid of the Russians-- because he was afraid he'd be sent to Siberia as a land owner-- some peasants came from Wilia to Ostrog, walking 25 kilometers, begging my father not to go away, and they will hide him.",
      "word_count": 53
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they will build-- they will dig a ditch, and they will hide entire family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And he said, look, it's enough to have one enemy there.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
